{"session_id":"svc-1778085754197036492","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T16:42:36.317695001Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-d0c656b0-20260506T164231-3fcc6761","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-d0c656b0\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ecli: add ddx bead queue top move clear\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;The spec now defines first-class queue movement commands, but operators still only have the generic `ddx bead update --set queue-rank=...` escape hatch. That forces humans to calculate ranks manually and does not protect priority semantics.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-beads.md:121-137 defines `ddx bead queue top`, `ddx bead queue move --before/--after`, and `ddx bead queue clear` semantics.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-beads.md:254-261 lists the CLI surface.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-beads.md:327-337 defines user-story acceptance for queue movement.\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/bead.go:46-65 registers bead subcommands but has no queue subcommand.\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/bead.go:448-540 supports generic update/set/unset but no command that computes sparse ranks or rejects cross-priority moves.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add `ddx bead queue` with `top \u0026lt;id\u0026gt;`, `move \u0026lt;id\u0026gt; --before \u0026lt;other-id\u0026gt;`, `move \u0026lt;id\u0026gt; --after \u0026lt;other-id\u0026gt;`, and `clear \u0026lt;id\u0026gt;`.\u0026#xA;- Implement sparse integer rank calculation: top assigns before the first ranked/effective bead in the same priority; before/after uses midpoint when possible; if no midpoint exists, renormalize only the affected priority bucket.\u0026#xA;- Reject before/after moves across different priorities with a clear error; priority changes remain explicit via `ddx bead update --priority`.\u0026#xA;- Persist queue-rank as a JSON number in Bead.Extra[\u0026#34;queue-rank\u0026#34;]; clear removes the key.\u0026#xA;- Register the subcommand in newBeadCommand.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not change Ready/ReadyExecution sorting in this bead; it depends on ddx-5ca2b0af.\u0026#xA;- Do not introduce a server-side picker or global queue table.\u0026#xA;- Do not add queue-rank to the core Bead struct or known schema field map.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestBeadQueueTopSetsRankWithoutChangingPriority verifies `ddx bead queue top \u0026lt;id\u0026gt;` persists numeric queue-rank and leaves Priority unchanged.\u0026#xA;2. TestBeadQueueMoveBeforeAfterUsesSparseRanks verifies before/after placement produces the expected ReadyExecution order without rewriting unrelated priority buckets.\u0026#xA;3. TestBeadQueueMoveRejectsCrossPriority verifies before/after across different priorities returns a clear error and does not mutate either bead.\u0026#xA;4. TestBeadQueueClearRemovesQueueRank verifies `ddx bead queue clear \u0026lt;id\u0026gt;` removes the key and default ordering resumes.\u0026#xA;5. TestBeadQueueRenormalizesOnlyPriorityBucket verifies midpoint exhaustion renormalizes only beads in the affected priority bucket.\u0026#xA;6. WIRED-IN: newBeadCommand registers `newBeadQueueCommand`, and `ddx bead queue --help` lists top, move, and clear.\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... -run \u0026#34;TestBeadQueue\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;8. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... ./internal/bead/... passes.\u0026#xA;9. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:cli, area:beads, kind:feature, spec:FEAT-004\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-0a47840f\" spec-id=\"FEAT-004\" base-rev=\"2a11386f5b4bbc26dc29c3835ca072c928bdeed8\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-004\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-beads.md\"\u003eFeature: Beads (Work Item Tracker)\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T164231-3fcc6761","base_rev":"2a11386f5b4bbc26dc29c3835ca072c928bdeed8","bead_id":"ddx-d0c656b0","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761","correlation_id":"ddx-d0c656b0:20260506T164231-3fcc6761","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260506T164231-3fcc6761/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"67bb87d71d04a58ba0fdb13a947fce053abb8bdf2d3c6027a165d97adac4be9f","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-8a779c0b","worker_id":""}}}
